# AITBC v0.5.0 Release Plan — Production Infrastructure

## Overview

v0.5.0 follows v0.4.27 and focuses on **infrastructure and state management** — the hardening that can't be done in a single session. v0.4.27 completes the quick wins (JWT migration, CI fixes). v0.5.0 tackles architecture changes.

**Target Date**: Q1 2025 (after v0.4.27)
**Theme**: "Harden the Foundation"
**Success Criteria**: All services are stateful, observable, and production-deployable.

---

## P0: DB/Redis Backing for Mock State

### Problem
Mock routers still use module-global `dict()` for state. This was deferred in v0.4.26 and v0.4.27. Production requires persistent, shared state.

### Affected Routers

| Router | State Type | Replacement |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| `routers/swarm.py` | `dict` of swarm configs | Redis hash |
| `routers/training.py` | `dict` of training jobs | Redis sorted set |
| `routers/hermes.py` | `dict` of message queues | Redis streams |
| `contexts/marketplace/services/marketplace_service.py` | In-memory offer cache | Redis cache |

### Work Required

| Task | Status | Owner |
|------|--------|-------|
| Design Redis schema for each state type | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Implement Redis-backed state manager | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Migrate training router to Redis | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Migrate hermes router to Redis | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Migrate swarm router to Redis | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add cache invalidation on state mutation | � Partial (clear_namespace method added) | Agent B |
| Ensure `debug=false` disables mock state creation | 🟡 Partial | Agent B |
| Migration script: migrate existing in-memory state | 🔴 Not started | TBD |

### Implementation Details

**New Files:**
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/services/redis_state.py` — Async Redis state manager with in-memory fallback

**Updated Files:**
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/config.py` — Added `RedisConfig` class with connection settings
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/routers/training.py` — Migrated `_mock_jobs` dict to Redis hash
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/routers/hermes.py` — Migrated `_mock_agents` and `_mock_messages` to Redis hash + list
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/routers/swarm.py` — Migrated to Redis hash for nodes, tasks, and clusters

**Redis Schema:**
| Namespace | Redis Type | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `aitbc:coordinator:training` | Hash | Training jobs |
| `aitbc:coordinator:hermes:agents` | Hash | Registered agents |
| `aitbc:coordinator:hermes:messages` | List | Message queues per agent |
| `aitbc:coordinator:swarm:nodes` | Hash | Compute nodes |
| `aitbc:coordinator:swarm:tasks` | Hash | Swarm tasks |
| `aitbc:coordinator:swarm:clusters` | Hash | Compute clusters |

### Acceptance Criteria
- [x] No module-global `dict()` for persistent state
- [x] State survives service restart (when Redis enabled)
- [x] Multiple coordinator instances share state via Redis
- [x] Graceful fallback to in-memory when Redis unavailable

