## P1: Systemd Hardening

### Problem
Systemd units were deferred in v0.4.26. Production services need security isolation.

### Work Required

| Task | Status | Owner |
|------|--------|-------|
| Audit all `.service` files | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add `PrivateTmp=yes` to all services | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add `NoNewPrivileges=yes` to all services | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add `ProtectSystem` (full/strict) to all services | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add `ProtectHome=yes` to all services | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add additional security directives | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add `WatchdogSec=30` + `NotifyAccess=all` | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Add `Restart=on-failure`, `RestartSec=5` | ✅ Complete | Agent B |
| Move secrets to `/etc/aitbc/%N.env` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Create `aitbc` user (non-root) for all services | 🔴 Not started | DevOps |

### Security Directives Added

All 31 service files hardened with:
- `PrivateTmp=yes` — isolated /tmp per service
- `NoNewPrivileges=yes` — prevent privilege escalation
- `ProtectHome=yes` — no home directory access
- `ProtectKernelTunables=yes` — read-only /proc/sys
- `ProtectKernelModules=yes` — no kernel module loading
- `ProtectControlGroups=yes` — read-only cgroupfs
- `RestrictSUIDSGID=yes` — no SUID/SGID binaries
- `RestrictRealtime=yes` — no real-time scheduling
- `RestrictNamespaces=yes` — no namespace creation
- `LockPersonality=yes` — no personality changes
- `MemoryDenyWriteExecute=yes` — no W^X violations
- `SystemCallArchitectures=native` — native arch only
- `SystemCallFilter=@system-service` — restricted syscalls
- `ProtectSystem=full` + `ReadWritePaths` (write-access services)
- `ProtectSystem=strict` (read-only services: P2P, plugin, load-secrets)
- `Restart=on-failure`, `RestartSec=5` (standardized from varying values)
- `WatchdogSec=30`, `NotifyAccess=all` (health monitoring)

### Files Changed
- All `apps/*/*.service` files
- `scripts/monitoring/aitbc-monitoring.service`
- `scripts/systemd/aitbc-recovery.service`
- `scripts/utils/*.service`
- `scripts/utils/harden-systemd-services.py` (automation script)
- `docs/releases/v0.5.0/systemd-hardening-report.md`

### Acceptance Criteria
- [x] All services have security hardening directives
- [x] `Restart=on-failure` standardized across all services
- [x] `RestartSec=5` standardized
- [ ] `systemd-analyze security` shows no "unsafe" services (requires deployment)
- [ ] No secrets in `/etc/systemd/system/*.service` (requires migration)
- [ ] All services run as `aitbc` user (requires DevOps)

